cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.DS, cs.PL 

This paper deals with a modal logic that is useful for encoding and reasoning about information and misinformation in multi-agent systems. This suggests that it could belong to the categories of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Multiagent Systems (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper presents an algebraic semantics and a cut-free sequent calculus, which are topics that fall under the categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Programming Languages (cs.PL).
